    <r3d:remarks>The Data Archive at the Max Planck Institute for Psycholinguistics is storing a lot of unique material, from a large variety of languages worldwide, which is recorded and analyzed by researchers from different linguistic disciplines. In particular the DOBES program on Documenting Endangered Languages funded by VolkswagenFoundation and the Digitization of the Human Ethology Archive from Irenäus Eibl-Eibesfeldt need to be mentioned.
The Language Archive is a regular member of the ICSU World Data System.
MPI is one of the CLARIN-D service centres. It&#039;s a part of the backbone of the German section of the CLARIN European research infrastructure federation.</r3d:remarks>
